@delaltar:
Look for "Final Cut Pro" on the disc image. Copy it to your applications folder. Double-click on the copy in the folder in future.

This download is not the installer. It's just the Final Cut Pro app. It doesn't contain the extra installations. An example is /System/Library/QuickTime/QuickTimeMPEG2.component. QuickTimeMPEG2 is automatically. installed by Lion and Mountain Lion, but that installation doesn't work with video editors like MPEG Streamclip. I've been looking just for the QuickTimeMPEG2 that Final Cut installs.

This download is just the Final Cut Pro app. If you need system files for it too, you need to get the Final Cut Pro installer. People seem to be saying, the app works on its own, though.
